Clarence Geldart https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clarence_Geldart 0 Clarence Geldart (June 9, 1867 – May 13, 1935) was an American film actor. He appeared in 127 films between 1915 and 1936. He is sometimes credited as C.H. Geldart or Charles H. Geldart. He was born in New Brunswick, Canada, and died in Calabasas, California. Geldart's Broadway credits include King Henry V (1900) and Beaucaire (1901). Clarence_Geldart ( June_9_,_1867 – May_13_,_1935 ) was an_American_film_actor .
